-- Germany’s KfW Group Helps Fund 53-Megawatt Wind Farm in Taiwan
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-09-24T08:40:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/germany-s-kfw-group-helps-fund-53-megawatt-wind-farm-in-taiwan.html
KfW Group,  Germany ’s state-owned
development bank, provided financing for a 52.9-megawatt wind
farm in  Taiwan  to be supplied by German turbine manufacturer
Enercon GmbH.  KfW’s IPEX export bank provided 66.8 million euros ($86
million) in loans to the Tongyuan wind farm on the country’s
west coast, the bank said today in an e-mailed statement. Total
investment for the project, which is being developed by
InfraVest GmbH and WPD AG and is to start operating in 2015, is
81.5 million euros, KfW Ipex said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
